    "goal_understanding": "The goal in each KA59 level is to get every selectable piece onto the goal tile(s) marked with a '+' at the same time; if there are multiple '+' tiles, all must be occupied simultaneously for the level to register WIN, and completing all levels wins the game.",
    "mechanics_understanding": "A single piece is \"selected\" at a time. Actions either use directional moves (e.g., MOVE_RIGHT) or CLICK on a target grid position. When movement is possible, the selected piece travels in a straight line to the intended square/stop; if the path is blocked by walls/obstacles/other blocking tiles (or the click has no valid movement effect), the piece does not move and the step is still consumed. CLICK can be used to attempt to move the selected piece toward/onto the clicked coordinate, while directional moves advance the selected piece in that direction until it reaches the next valid stopping point. Steps per level are limited, so wasted/blocked moves can end the run."
